In [[telecommunication]], the term '''call delay''' has the following meanings: 

#The [[delay]] that occurs when a [[call]] arrives at an automatic [[switching]] device and no [[channel (communications)|channel]] or [[facility]] is immediately available to process the call. 
#The [[time]] between the instant a [[system]] receives a [[call attempt]] and the instant of initiation of ringing at the [[call receiver]] [[end instrument]].